@extends('index')
@section('title')
How to use Heroku after the GitHub auto-deploy desync
@endsection
@section('content')
<p>On april Heroku suffered a big glitch abuse where some users got access to many private repositories that were connected to 
Heroku, Heroku quickly deactivated the connection between the two platforms and many users were left on tied hands. But there's still 
a way to use both platforms together, here I am going to show how.
</p>
<h2>What you will need to use:</h2>
<ul>
    <li>A GitHub account with your projects repository on it.</li>
    <li>A Heroku account</li>
    <li>The Git installed in your machine.</li>
    <li>The Heroku CLI installed in your machine.</li>
</ul>

<br/>

<h2>Create your Heroku Project</h2>
