<p>This step is really easy, just create a project on Heroku.</p>

<h2>Open your repository locally and create the Heroku remote </h2>
<p>To create the remote enter inside your command line: <code>heroku git:remote -a your-app-name</code></p>

<h2>Deploy your project on Heroku</h2>
<p>Now your repository is connected to Heroku, to deploy it just enter inside the command line: <code>git push heroku main
</code> and that's it!</p>
